維基解密於2006年創立。<ref name="khatchadourian" /><ref name="smh2">{{cite news | title = The secret life of Wikileaks founder Julian Assange | url = http://www.smh.com.au/technology/technology-news/the-secret-life-of-wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-20100521-w1um.html | date = 2010-05-22 | newspaper = The Sydney Morning Herald | accessdate = 2010-06-16 | archive-date = 2017-11-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171113005256/http://www.smh.com.au/technology/technology-news/the-secret-life-of-wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-20100521-w1um.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>它是阿桑奇個人思想的凝集。在同年阿桑奇所寫的兩篇文章中，他對於維基解密的創辦動機是這樣解釋的：

{{quote|width=70%|爲了徹底改變政權的行事方法，我們必須認真、大膽地思考應採取的策略。前人的經歷已經告訴我們，政權自身是不希望發生改變的。我們要超越前人的思維，從新科技中獲取啓發，尋找出對我們有用的、前人沒有機會用到的技術。<ref name="Whelan">{{cite web| url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1299311/FBI-question-WikiLeaks-mother-Welsh-home-Agent-interrogate-distressed-woman-search-sons-bedroom.html| title = FBI question WikiLeaks mother at Welsh home: Agents interrogate 'distressed' woman, then search her son's bedroom| author = Andy Whelan and Sharon Churcher| date = 2010-08-01| accessdate = 2010-12-01| archive-date = 2021-03-09| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210309172048/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1299311/FBI-question-WikiLeaks-mother-Welsh-home-Agent-interrogate-distressed-woman-search-sons-bedroom.html| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://iq.org/conspiracies.pdf | title = State and Terrorist Conspiracies | first = Julian | last = Assange | date = 2006-11-10 | accessdate = 2010-12-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070829163014/http://iq.org/conspiracies.pdf | archive-date = 2007-08-29 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url = http://web.archive.org/web/20070129125831/iq.org/conspiracies.pdf | title = Conspiracy as Governance |first = Julian| last = Assange| date =2006-12-03| accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref>}}

在他的[https://web.archive.org/web/20071020051936/http://iq.org/ 個人網站]上，他還寫道：

{{quote|width=70%|某個組織越是隱秘，越是對事件採取諱莫如深的態度，信息的洩露就越能引致組織內部、小圈子的驚惶與無端的恐懼……因為，不公平的系統的產物一定是眾多的異議人士。與異議者相比之下，組織的操控者還常常占寡數和劣勢。這種情況下將系統的大量秘密信息洩露，會使這一不公正的系統，在其他更加開放的系統面前，顯得更加的脆弱與不穩定。<ref name="Whelan" /><ref>{{cite web | url = http://iq.org | title = The non linear effects of leaks on unjust systems of governance | date = 2006-12-31 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071020051936/http://iq.org/ | archivedate = 2007-10-20 | access-date = 2007-10-20 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>}}

[[File:26C3_Assange_DomscheitBerg.jpg|thumb]]在柏林的[[混沌通讯大会|混沌通讯大会]](26C3)]]

阿桑奇是維基解密的9名顧問組成員之一，<ref name="advisory">{{cite web | title = WikiLeaks:Advisory Board | url = http://wikileaks.org/wiki/WikiLeaks:Advisory_Board | publisher = Wikileaks | accessdate = 2010-06-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100617033041/http://www.wikileaks.org/wiki/WikiLeaks:Advisory_Board | archive-date = 2010-06-17 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>而且是維基解密最主要的發言人。他自己儘量迴避“創始人”的稱呼，<ref name="leakonomy">Interview with Julian Assange, spokesperson of WikiLeaks: [http://stefanmey.wordpress.com/2010/01/04/leak-o-nomy-the-economy-of-WikiLeaks ''Leak-o-nomy: The Economy of WikiLeaks''] {{Wayback|url=http://stefanmey.wordpress.com/2010/01/04/leak-o-nomy-the-economy-of-WikiLeaks |date=20100524131035 }}</ref>僅稱自己是維基解密的主編，<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/tedtalks/julian-assange-why-the-wo_b_651329.html | title = Julian Assange: Why the World Needs WikiLeaks | publisher = Huffington Post | date = 2010-07-19 | accessdate = 2010-08-22 | archive-date = 2016-09-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160913144216/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/tedtalks/julian-assange-why-the-wo_b_651329.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>並對維基解密收到的文件審查工作享有最終的決定權。<ref name="motherjones">{{cite news | title = Inside WikiLeaks' Leak Factory | url = http://motherjones.com/politics/2010/04/wikileaks-julian-assange-iraq-video?page=1 | first = David | last = Kushner | date = 2010-04-06 | newspaper = [[Mother_Jones_(magazine)|Mother Jones]] | accessdate = 2010-06-16 | archive-date = 2016-08-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160820210622/http://www.motherjones.com/politics/2010/04/wikileaks-julian-assange-iraq-video?page=1 | dead-url = no }}</ref>為維基解密工作是沒有收入的，一如維基解密的其他職員。<ref name="leakonomy" /><ref>[http://www.wikileaks.org/wiki/WikiLeaks:Advisory_Board#Julian_Assange.2C_investigative_journalist.2C_programmer_and_activist WikiLeaks:Advisory Board – Julian Assange, investigative journalist, programmer and activist] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wikileaks.org/wiki/WikiLeaks:Advisory_Board#Julian_Assange.2C_investigative_journalist.2C_programmer_and_activist |date=20100912101437 }}（short biography on the Wikileaks home page）</ref><ref>[http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,2006496,00.html Harrell, Eben，（26 July 2010）''2-Min. Bio WikiLeaks Founder Julian Assange'' 26 July 2010] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,2006496,00.html |date=20130825145220 }} ''[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]''.</ref><ref>[http://www.democracynow.org/2010/6/17/wikileaks_whistleblowers Rumored Manhunt for Wikileaks Founder and Arrest of Alleged Leaker of Video Showing Iraq Killings] {{Wayback|url=http://www.democracynow.org/2010/6/17/wikileaks_whistleblowers |date=20210126021146 }} – video report by ''[[Democracy_Now!|Democracy Now!]]''</ref><ref>{{cite web | author = Adheesha Sarkar | url = http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100810/jsp/opinion/story_12789816.jsp | title = The People'S Spy | publisher = Telegraphindia.com | date = 2010-08-10 | accessdate = 2010-08-22 | archive-date = 2016-03-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304205812/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100810/jsp/opinion/story_12789816.jsp | dead-url = no }}</ref>

