2018年1月11日，厄瓜多尔外交部长玛丽亚·埃斯皮诺萨称，厄瓜多尔政府已于2017年底授予阿桑奇厄瓜多尔公民身份。预计厄瓜多尔政府接下来会授予阿桑奇外交人员身份，这样阿桑奇即拥有外交豁免权，便可离开位于英国伦敦[[骑士桥|骑士桥]]的厄瓜多尔驻英大使馆，阿桑奇依旧拥有澳大利亚国籍。

=== 在大使馆的后期 ===
[[File:Transmisioncorrea.jpg|thumb]](Rafael Correa)於2007年至2017年擔任厄瓜多爾總統.]]

2017年3月，維基解密開始發布歷史上最大的[[中央情报局|中央情报局]] (CIA) 文件洩露事件，代號為"{{link-en|七號保險庫|Vault 7}}(Vault 7)"。這些文件包括 CIA [[網絡戰|黑客能力]]和用於侵入智能手機、計算機和其他互聯網連接設備的軟件工具的詳細信息<ref name="nyt070317">{{cite news |last1=Shane |first1=Scott |last2=Rosenberg |first2=Matthew |last3=Lehren |first3=Andrew W. |title=WikiLeaks Releases Trove of Alleged C.I.A. Hacking Documents |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/07/world/europe/wikileaks-cia-hacking.html |access-date=2020-09-11 |work=The New York Times |date=2017-03-07 |archive-date=2017-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307212004/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/07/world/europe/wikileaks-cia-hacking.html }}</ref>。4月，中央情報局局長[[邁克·蓬佩奧|邁克·蓬佩奧]]（Mike Pompeo）稱維基解密是“一個經常受到俄羅斯等國家教唆的{{le|非國家主體|Non-state actor|非國家}}敵對[[情報機構|情報機構]]”<ref>{{cite news |title=CIA chief calls WikiLeaks a 'hostile intelligence service' |author=Warren Strobel |author2=Mark Hosenball |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cia-wikileaks-idUSKBN17F2L8 |work=[[Reuters|Reuters]] |date=2017-04-13 |accessdate=2022-02-03 |archive-date=2022-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220621090237/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cia-wikileaks-idUSKBN17F2L8 }}</ref>。阿桑奇指責中央情報局試圖“顛覆”他的言論自由權<ref>{{cite news |title=Assange lashes out against CIA after Pompeo rips WikiLeaks |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/assange-lashes-out-against-cia-after-pompeo-rips-wikileaks |publisher=Fox News Channel |date=2017-04-15 |accessdate=2022-02-03 |archive-date=2022-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220621090153/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/assange-lashes-out-against-cia-after-pompeo-rips-wikileaks }}</ref>。 據前情報官員稱，在"7號避難所(Vault 7)"洩密後，中央情報局密謀從厄瓜多爾倫敦大使館綁架阿桑奇，一些高級官員討論了他可能被暗殺的可能性。[[雅虎新闻|雅虎新闻]]發現“沒有跡象表明針對阿桑奇的最極端措施曾經獲得批准。” 它的一些消息來源稱，他們已向[[美国众议院情报委员会|眾議院]]和[[參議院情報委員會|參議院情報委員會]]通報了蓬佩奧提出的計劃<ref name=IsikYahoo21>{{cite web |url=https://news.yahoo.com/kidnapping-assassination-and-a-london-shoot-out-inside-the-ci-as-secret-war-plans-against-wiki-leaks-090057786.html |title=Kidnapping, assassination and a London shoot-out: Inside the CIA's secret war plans against WikiLeaks |publisher=[[Yahoo!_News|Yahoo! News]] |date=2021-09-26 |access-date=2021-09-26 |last1=Dorfman |first1=Zach |last2=Naylor |first2=Sean D. |last3=Isikoff |first3=Michael |archive-date=2021-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210927155859/https://news.yahoo.com/kidnapping-assassination-and-a-london-shoot-out-inside-the-ci-as-secret-war-plans-against-wiki-leaks-090057786.html }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bourke|first=Latika|date=2021-09-27|title=Trump administration floated kidnapping, killing Julian Assange: report|url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/trump-administration-floated-kidnapping-killing-julian-assange-report-20210927-p58v72.html|access-date=2021-09-30|work=[[The_Sydney_Morning_Herald|The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|archive-date=2022-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623035339/https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/trump-administration-floated-kidnapping-killing-julian-assange-report-20210927-p58v72.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Grim |first1=Ryan |last2=Sirota |first2=Sara |title=Julian Assange Kidnapping Plot Casts New Light on 2018 Senate Intelligence Maneuver |url=https://theintercept.com/2021/09/28/assange-kidnapping-wikileaks-cia-senate/ |work=[[The_Intercept|The Intercept]] |location=New York |publisher=[[First_Look_Media|First Look Media]] |date=2021-09-28 |accessdate=2022-02-03 |archive-date=2021-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210930160636/https://theintercept.com/2021/09/28/assange-kidnapping-wikileaks-cia-senate/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=White|first=Debbie|work=[[The_Times|The Times]]|location=London|title=CIA 'discussed kidnapping or assassinating Wikileaks founder Julian Assange'|language=en|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/cia-discussed-kidnapping-or-assassinating-wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-n3x50hcsz|access-date=2021-09-30|issn=0140-0460|archive-date=2021-09-27|archive-