逮捕行动过后，阿桑奇被关押在伦敦{{tsl|en|HM Prison Belmarsh|贝尔马什监狱}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-48118908|title=Julian Assange jailed over bail breach|date=2019-05-01|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623164202/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-48118908}}</ref>。

联合国酷刑及其他残忍、不人道或有辱人格的待遇或处罚特别报告员{{tsl|en|Nils Melzer|尼尔斯·梅尔泽}}于2019年5月9日对阿桑奇进行身体检查，发现阿桑奇除了身体疾病，还出现了所有长期暴露于{{tsl|en|psychological torture|心理折磨}}的典型症状，包括高度紧张、慢性焦虑和强烈的心理创伤<ref>{{cite news |last1=Stanley-Becker |first1=Isaac |last2=Booth |first2=William |title=U.N. official says Julian Assange is a victim of 'psychological torture,' warns against U.S. extradition |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/un-official-says-assange-is-a-victim-ofpsychological-torture-warns-against-extradition-to-the-us/2019/05/31/cca722e0-5f84-11e9-bf24-db4b9fb62aa2_story.html |access-date=2021-10-05 |newspaper=Washington Post |date=2019-05-31 |archive-date=2022-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220041535/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/un-official-says-assange-is-a-victim-ofpsychological-torture-warns-against-extradition-to-the-us/2019/05/31/cca722e0-5f84-11e9-bf24-db4b9fb62aa2_story.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|website=United Nations Human Rights: Office of the High Commissioner|author=Nils Melzer|date=2019-05-31|access-date=2019-05-31|url=https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=24665&LangID=E|title=UN expert says 'collective persecution' of Julian Assange must end now|archive-date=2022-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220308154836/https://ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=24665&LangID=E}}</ref>。英国政府不认同梅尔泽的部分观察结果<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cumming-Bruce |first1=Nick |title=Julian Assange Is Suffering Psychological Torture, U.N. Expert Says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/31/world/europe/julian-assange-torture-un.html |work=The New York Times |date=2019-05-31 |accessdate=2022-02-04 |archive-date=2022-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220620230655/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/31/world/europe/julian-assange-torture-un.html }}</ref>。在其后的采访中，梅尔泽批评“美国大陪审团进行秘密起诉”、“瑞典检察官以滥用方式传播、再循环和延续他们对涉嫌性犯罪的‘初步调查’”、“厄瓜多尔在没有任何形式的正当程序的情况下终止了阿桑奇先生的庇护身份和公民身份”、“英国法官自逮捕行动以来对阿桑奇先生表现出明显的偏见”。他认为上述四方想让阿桑奇以儆效尤。他还指控记者“散布辱骂性及故意歪曲的叙述”<ref>{{cite news |last1=McEvoy |first1=John |title=UN torture expert says Assange's persecution 'very similar to historic witch-hunts' in exclusive interview |url=https://www.thecanary.co/feature/2019/06/06/un-torture-expert-says-assanges-persecution-very-similar-to-historic-witch-hunts-in-exclusive-interview/ |access-date=2019-06-13 |publisher=The Canary |date=2019-06-06 |archive-date=2022-06-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220622151306/https://www.thecanary.co/feature/2019/06/06/un-torture-expert-says-assanges-persecution-very-similar-to-historic-witch-hunts-in-exclusive-interview/ }}</ref>。不久之后，阿桑奇被转移到私人医护病房<ref name="ohchr25249">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=25249&LangID=E|title=OHCHR | UN expert on torture sounds alarm again that Julian Assange's life may be at risk|website=ohchr.org|access-date=2022-02-04|archive-date=2022-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313015751/https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=25249&LangID=E}}</ref>。

2019年9月13日，地方法官凡妮莎·巴雷策（Vanessa Baraitser）裁定阿桑奇不能在9月22日刑期届满当天获释，因为他有飞行风险，而且律师也没有申请保释<ref name="guardian140919">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/sep/14/julian-assange-to-remain-in-jail-pending-extradition-to-us|title=Julian Assange to remain in jail pending extradition to US|work=The Guardian|date=2019-09-14|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2021-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130060919/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/sep/14/julian-assange-to-remain-in-jail-pending-extradition-to-us}}</ref>，故阿桑奇到时身份会从在囚囚犯转变成亟待引渡人士<ref name="guardian140919"/>。

2019年11月1日，梅尔泽表示阿桑奇健康状况正持续恶化，生命受到威胁<ref name="abc021119">{{cite news |title=Julian Assange's treatment in prison putting his life at risk, UN rights expert warns |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-11-02/treatment-of-assange-putting-his-life-at-risk-un-expert/11666400 |access-date=2019-11-07 |agency=Agence France-Presse |publisher=ABC News (Australia) |date=2019-11-02 |archive-date=2022-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618001622/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-11-02/treatment-of-assange-putting-his-life-at-risk-un-expert/11666400 }}</ref><ref name="ohchr25249"/>。他表示英当局没有采取行动应对问题<ref name="abc021119" /><ref name="ohchr25249"/>。

11月22日，“医生为阿桑奇”（Doctors for Assange）团体向[[內政大臣_(英國)|英国内政大臣]]及{{tsl|en|Shadow Home Secretary|影子内政大臣}}发出联署公开信，表示阿桑奇健康持续恶化，可能会死在监狱里<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/nov/25/julian-assanges-health-is-so-bad-he-could-die-in-prison-say-60-doctors|title=Julian Assange's health is so bad he 'could die in prison', say 60 doctors|access-date=2019-11-25|website=The Guardian|date=2019-11-25|archive-date=2022-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220628174218/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/nov/25/julian-assanges-health-is-so-bad-he-could-die-in-prison-say-60-doctors}}</ref>。团体之后向[[大法官_(英國)|大法官]]兼司法大臣[[羅伯特·巴克蘭|羅伯特·巴克蘭]]<ref>{{cite web |first= John |last= McEvoy |url= https://www.thecanary.co/uk/news/2019/12/04/medical-doctors-lambast-home-secretarys-failure-to-respond-to-concerns-over-julian-assange/ |title= Medical doctors lambast home secretary's failure to respond to concerns over Julian Assange |date= 2019-12-04 |website= The Canary |access-date= 2020-06-29 |archive-date= 2022-06-17 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220617165623/https://www.thecanary.co/uk/news/2019/12/04/medical-doctors-lambast-home-secretarys-failure-to-respond-to-concerns-over-julian-assange/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2019/12/05/doct-d05.html |title= Doctors condemn failure of British government to answer letter demanding medical care for Julian Assange |website= [[世界社會主義網站|World Socialist Web Site]] |date= 2019-12-05 |access-date= 2020-06-29 |archive-date= 2022-04-09 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065209/https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2019/12/05/doct-d05.html }}</ref>和{{tsl|en|Minister for Foreign Affairs (Australia)|澳大利亚外交部长}}[[马里斯·佩恩|马里斯·佩恩]]发去公开信，均未获回复<ref>{{cite news |first1= Rob |last1= Harris |first2= Bevan |last2= Shields |url= https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/doctors-ask-government-to-evacuate-assange-to-an-australian-hospital-20191216-p53k8z.html |title= Doctors ask government to evacuate Assange to an Australian hospital |work= The Sydney Morning Herald |date= 2019-12-17 |access-date= 2020-06-29 |archive-date= 2022-04-09 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065208/https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/doctors-ask-government-to-evacuate-assange-to-an-australian-hospital-20191216-p53k8z.html }}</ref>。

2019年12月30日，梅尔泽指控英国政府虐待阿桑奇，表示阿桑奇“持续遭受严重的精神和情感痛苦……（这些待遇）显然构成心理折磨或其他残忍、不人道或有辱人格的待遇或处罚”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spcommreports.ohchr.org/TMResultsBase/DownLoadPublicCommunicationFile?gId=24926|title=Mandate of the Special Rapporteur on torture and other cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or punishment|first=Nils|last=Melzer|work=OHCHR|date=2019-10-29|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519205032/https://spcommreports.ohchr.org/TMResultsBase/DownLoadPublicCommunicationFile?gId=24926}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/wikileaks-julian-assange-chelsea-manning-torture-un-detention-whistleblower-nils-melzer-a9266076.html|title=WikiLeaks: UN official accuses UK and US of torture over treatment of Assange and Manning|first=Andrew|last=Buncombe|date=2019-12-31|work=The Independent|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065208/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/wikileaks-julian-assange-chelsea-manning-torture-un-detention-whistleblower-nils-melzer-a9266076.html}}</ref>。

2020年2月17日，医学期刊《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|柳叶刀]]》刊登“医生为阿桑奇”团体的公开信<ref>{{cite journal|vauthors= Frost S, Johnson L, Stein J, Frost W, et al.|date= 2020-02-19 |title= End torture and medical neglect of Julian Assange |journal= [[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|The Lancet]] |volume= 395 |issue= 10226 |pages= e44–e45 |doi= 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30383-4 |pmid= 32078804 |s2cid= 211141391 |issn= 0140-6736 |doi-access= free }}</ref>，表示阿桑奇的健康状况因厄瓜多尔大使馆及贝尔马什监狱的长期虐待而急剧恶化<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-au/news/world/doctors-call-for-end-of-assange-torture/ar-BB106b9w|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218153606/https://www.msn.com/en-au/news/world/doctors-call-for-end-of-assange-torture/ar-BB106b9w|url-status=dead|archive-date=2020-02-18|title=Doctors call for end of Assange 'torture'|first=Padraig|last=Collins|date=2020-02-18|publisher=MSN News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/julian-assange-could-be-effectively-tortured-to-death-in-belmarsh-doctors-claim-11936883|title=Julian Assange 'in dire state of health due to psychological torture', doctors claim|first=Emily|last=Mee|date=2020-02-18|publisher=Sky News|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065209/https://news.sky.com/story/julian-assange-could-be-effectively-tortured-to-death-in-belmarsh-doctors-claim-11936883}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/de/%C3%A4rzte-kritisieren-haft-von-wikileaks-gr%C3%BCnder-assange-als-folter/a-52412264|language=de|title=Ärzte kritisieren Haft von Wikileaks-Gründer Assange als Folter|date=2020-02-18|publisher=Deutsche Welle|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422152544/https://www.dw.com/de/%C3%A4rzte-kritisieren-haft-von-wikileaks-gr%C3%BCnder-assange-als-folter/a-52412264}}</ref>。同日，[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]发表另一份联署，指控特朗普政府“报复阿桑奇的行为促使国际媒体对美国进行战争的方式进行重大披露”。联署认为阿桑奇披露的情报“完全是出于公共利益，不是间谍举动”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/02/566644/doctors-media-freedom-group-rally-around-assange|title=Doctors, media freedom group rally around Assange|date=2020-02-18|publisher=New Straits Times|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065212/https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/02/566644/doctors-media-freedom-group-rally-around-assange}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200218-m%C3%A9decins-et-journalistes-apportent-leur-soutien-%C3%A0-julian-assange|language=fr|title=Médecins et journalistes apportent leur soutien à Julian Assange|date=2020-02-18|publisher=France 24|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065209/https://www.france24.com/fr/20200218-m%C3%A9decins-et-journalistes-apportent-leur-soutien-%C3%A0-julian-assange}}</ref>。澳洲议员[[安德魯·威爾基|安德魯·威爾基]]和[[喬治·克里斯滕森|喬治·克里斯滕森]]在探视阿桑奇后要求英国和澳大利亚政府出面干涉引渡阿桑奇的过程<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/18/julian-assange-australian-mps-uk-boris-johnson-block-us-extradition|title=Julian Assange: Australian MPs call on UK to block US extradition|first=Ben|last=Quinn|date=2020-02-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065209/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/18/julian-assange-australian-mps-uk-boris-johnson-block-us-extradition}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/6635833/uk-pm-johnson-urged-to-end-assange-trial/|title=UK PM Johnson urged to end Assange trial|first=Marty|last=Silk|date=2020-02-18|publisher=The Canberra Times|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065214/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/6635833/uk-pm-johnson-urged-to-end-assange-trial/}}</ref>。

2020年3月25日，法官巴莱策驳回了阿桑奇律师就[[COVID-19疫情|COVID-19疫情]]提交的保释申请<ref name=baildenied>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-britain-assange/wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-denied-bail-by-london-court-idUSKBN21C266|title=Wikileaks founder Julian Assange denied bail by London court|publisher=Reuters|date=2020-03-25|access-date=2020-03-25|archive-date=2022-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220416062214/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-britain-assange/wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-denied-bail-by-london-court-idUSKBN21C266}}</ref>。法官表示，阿桑奇过去的行为证明他会不惜一切代价逃避引渡<ref name=baildenied />。2021年11月，阿桑奇父亲向法国媒体表示阿桑奇自愿接种监狱提供的COVID-19疫苗<ref>{{cite web |url=https://consortiumnews.com/2021/11/16/assanges-father-says-his-son-has-been-vaccinated/ |title=Assange's Father Says His Son Has Been Vaccinated |work=Consortium News |date=2021-11-16 |access-date=2021-11-16 |author=Lauria, Joe |archive-date=2022-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065208/https://consortiumnews.com/2021/11/16/assanges-father-says-his-son-has-been-vaccinated/ }}</ref>。

2020年6月25日，“医生为阿桑奇”再次在《柳叶刀》刊登公开信，要求结束对阿桑奇的虐待及医疗忽视<ref>{{cite journal|vauthors= Hogan W, Frost S, Johnson L, Schulze T, Nelson E, Frost W, et al.|date= 2020-06-25 |title= The ongoing torture and medical neglect of Julian Assange |journal= [[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|The Lancet]] |volume= 396 |issue= 10243 |pages= 22–23 |doi= 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31444-6 |pmid= 32593324 |pmc= 7316471 |s2cid= 220056656 |url= |issn= 0140-6736 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1= Untersinger |first1= Martin |date= 2020-06-26 |title= Des médecins dénoncent la 'torture' subie par Julian Assange, le fondateur de WikiLeaks |trans-title= Doctors denounce the 'torture' suffered by WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange |url= https://www.lemonde.fr/pixels/article/2020/06/26/des-medecins-denoncent-la-torture-subie-par-julian-assange-le-fondateur-de-wikileaks_6044278_4408996.html |language= fr |work= [[世界报_(法国)|Le Monde]] |location= Paris |access-date= 2020-06-29 |archive-date= 2022-06-29 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220629064256/https://www.lemonde.fr/pixels/article/2020/06/26/des-medecins-denoncent-la-torture-subie-par-julian-assange-le-fondateur-de-wikileaks_6044278_4408996.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date= 2020-06-25 |title= Doctors for Assange Say UK May be Liable for His Torture |url= https://consortiumnews.com/2020/06/25/doctors-for-assange-say-uk-may-be-liable-for-his-torture/ |work= Consortium News |access-date= 2020-06-29 |archive-date= 2022-04-09 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065227/https://consortiumnews.com/2020/06/25/doctors-for-assange-say-uk-may-be-liable-for-his-torture/ }}</ref>。2020年9月，2名现任政府首脑与约160名政界人士向英国首相[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]发出支持阿桑奇的公开信<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/wikileaks-julian-assange-letter-uk-prison-leaders-b519304.html|title=More than 160 world leaders and diplomats call for UK to release Julian Assange|first=Graeme|last=Massie|work=The Independent|date=2020-09-22|access-date=2020-10-07|archive-date=2022-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220426085605/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/wikileaks-julian-assange-letter-uk-prison-leaders-b519304.html}}</ref>。次月，美国民主党籍众议员[[图尔西·加巴德|图尔西·加巴德]]与共和党籍众议员[[托馬斯·馬西|托馬斯·馬西]]提出一项反对引渡阿桑奇的决议<ref>{{cite web|url=http://njtoday.net/2020/10/05/congress-moves-to-save-journalism/|title=Congress moves to save journalism|publisher=NJ Today|date=2020-10-05|access-date=2020-10-07|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421035824/http://njtoday.net/2020/10/05/congress-moves-to-save-journalism/}}</ref>。2020年12月，德国人权专员[[芭貝爾·柯夫勒|芭貝爾·柯夫勒]]提请英国在做出是否引渡的决定前考虑阿桑奇的身心健康<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/germany-urges-uk-to-uphold-human-rights-in-assange-case/a-56098705|title=Germany urges UK to uphold human rights in Assange case|author=Melissa Sou-Jie Brunnersum|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=2020-12-30|access-date=2021-01-03|archive-date=2022-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409065227/https://www.dw.com/en/germany-urges-uk-to-uphold-human-rights-in-assange-case/a-56098705}}</ref>。

=== 引渡至美國的聽證會 ===
[[File:Oldbaileylondon-900.jpg|thumb]]的中央刑事法院]]
2019年5月2日，伦敦就引渡阿桑奇至美国的问题举行首场听证会。在被法官斯诺（Snow）问到是否同意引渡时，阿桑奇表示“不想因为赢得许多大奖、保护了许多人的新闻报道自愿引渡”<ref name="guardian020519">{{cite news |last1=Quinn |first1=Ben |title=US begins extradition case against Julian Assange in London |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/may/02/us-begins-noextradition-case-against-julian-assange-in-london |access-date=2020-10-07 |work=The Guardian |date=2019-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-48134901 | title=Julian Assange doesn't consent to US extradition, court hears | date=2019-05-02 | access-date=2019-05-03 | publisher=BBC | archive-date=2022-06-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220621063242/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-48134901 }}</ref>。6月13日，内政大臣[[薩吉德·賈偉德|薩吉德·賈偉德]]表示已签署引渡令<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/jun/13/julian-assange-sajid-javid-signs-us-extradition-order|title=Sajid Javid signs US extradition order for Julian Assange|first=Matthew|last=Weaver|work=The Guardian|date=2019-06-13|access-date=2022-02-04|archive-date=2022-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220620194747/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/jun/13/julian-assange-sajid-javid-signs-us-extradition-order}}</ref>。

到2019年年底，主审多场引渡听证会的{{tsl|en|Emma Arbuthnot|艾玛·阿巴思诺特}}法官因“认知偏见”回避<ref name="dm030920">{{cite news |last1=Curtis |first1=Mark |last2=Kennard |first2=Matt |title=Declassified UK: As British judge made rulings against Julian Assange, her husband was involved with right-wing lobby group briefing against WikiLeaks founder |url=https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2020-09-04-as-british-judge-made-rulings-against-julian-assange-her-husband-was-involved-with-right-wing-lobby-group-briefing-against-wikileaks-founder/ |access-date=2020-10-12 |work=Daily Maverick |date=2020-09-03 |language=en |archive-date=2022-05-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220530223159/https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2020-09-04-as-british-judge-made-rulings-against-julian-assange-her-husband-was-involved-with-right-wing-lobby-group-briefing-against-wikileaks-founder/ }}</ref>，由凡妮莎·巴雷策接任<ref name="dm030920"/>。

2019年10月21日，阿桑奇出席案件管理聆讯。被法官巴雷策问到对司法程序的理解时，阿桑奇回复：

{{blockquote|我不明白这怎么能叫公平。那个超级大国已经为这个案件准备了10年之久，而且我还不能拿到我的著作。我现在这幅模样做什么事情都很艰难，但那些人有着无尽的资源。他们老是说记者和吹哨人是人民的敌人。他们有着处理（案件）文件的超人优势。他们（知道）我和我的心理医生过着怎样的生活，他们偷了我孩子们的DNA。这样的事情还能叫公平吗？<ref name="Busby 2019">{{cite web | last=Busby | first=Mattha | title=Julian Assange extradition judge refuses request for delay | website=The Guardian | date=2019-10-21 | url=http://www.theguardian.com/media/2019/oct/21/julian-assange-extradition-judge-refuses-request-for-delay-wikileaks | access-date=2021-05-11}}</ref>}}

2020年2月，法院听取法律论据<ref name="bbc-7-sept-2020"/>。律师认为阿桑奇身负政治指控，不能引渡<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/27/julian-assanges-lawyers-us-files-were-leaked-for-political-ends|title=Julian Assange's lawyers: US files were leaked for political ends|first=Frances|last=Perraudin|work=The Guardian|date=2020-02-28|accessdate=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618061616/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/27/julian-assanges-lawyers-us-files-were-leaked-for-political-ends}}</ref>。受COVID-19疫情影响，加上控辩双方要求额外准备时间，听证会推迟数月举行<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-assange/extradition-hearing-for-wikileaks-assange-to-be-split-in-two-parts-idUSKBN1ZM1LN|title=Extradition hearing for WikiLeaks' Assange to be split in two parts|publisher=Reuters|date=2020-01-23|accessdate=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618061610/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-assange/extradition-hearing-for-wikileaks-assange-to-be-split-in-two-parts-idUSKBN1ZM1LN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/assange-s-extradition-hearing-delayed-by-lawyer-s-wife-s-covid-scare-20200910-p55uil.html|title=Assange's extradition hearing delayed by lawyer's wife's COVID scare|first=Latika|last=Bourke|publisher=Sydney Morning Herald|date=2020-09-10|accessdate=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618061611/https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/assange-s-extradition-hearing-delayed-by-lawyer-s-wife-s-covid-scare-20200910-p55uil.html}}</ref>。3月，[[国际律师协会|国际律师协会]]人权研究院谴责当局在引渡审判中虐待阿桑奇<ref name="ibahri">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibanet.org/Article/NewDetail.aspx?ArticleUid=c05c57ee-1fee-47dc-99f9-26824208a750|title=IBAHRI condemns UK treatment of Julian Assange in US extradition trial|publisher=IBAHRI|access-date=2022-06-18|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108082608/https://www.ibanet.org/Article/NewDetail.aspx?ArticleUid=C05C57EE-1FEE-47DC-99F9-26824208A750}}</ref>。

2020年9月7日，法庭为阿桑奇公布了18项新指控，包括一项合谋获取、披露国防信息罪、一项合谋入侵计算机罪、七项获取国防信息罪及九项披露国防信息罪<ref name="doj-assange-june-2020">{{cite web |title=WikiLeaks Founder Charged in Superseding Indictment |url=https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/wikileaks-founder-charged-superseding-indictment |publisher=United States Department of Justice |access-date=2020-09-29 |date=2020-06-24 |archive-date=2022-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220627213104/https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/wikileaks-founder-charged-superseding-indictment }}</ref>。美国司法部表示，新的起诉书“扩大了……涉嫌计算机入侵的范围”，显示阿桑奇与黑客组织[[LulzSec|LulzSec]]的头目有直接联系，向组织提供了黑客目标清单，与陆军情报分析师切尔西·曼宁（Chelsea Manning）合谋破解[[密钥派生函数|密码哈希值]]<ref name="doj-assange-june-2020"/>。针对阿桑奇律师提出的否认新指控或暂停审理留待回应的动议，巴雷策法官驳回<ref name="bbc-7-sept-2020">{{cite web |title=Julian Assange appears in dock as extradition hearing resumes |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-54060427 |publisher=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2020-09-28 |date=2020-09-07 |archive-date=2022-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618061606/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-54060427 }}</ref>。9月，[[丹尼尔·艾尔斯伯格|丹尼尔·艾尔斯伯格]]等多位证人透过视频会议方式作证。受技术问题影响，作证过程被大量延误<ref name="nyt-specia-sept-16">{{cite web |last1=Specia |first1=Megan |title=At Assange's Extradition Hearing, Troubled Tech Takes Center Stage |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/16/world/europe/assange-extradition-hearing.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=2020-09-28 |date=2020-09-16 |archive-date=2022-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220618061606/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/16/world/europe/assange-extradition-hearing.html }}</ref>。[[國際特赦組織|國際特赦組織]]、[[国际笔会|国际笔会]]挪威分会与八位[[歐洲議會議員|歐洲議會議員]]被剥夺了观看庭审直播的权限，对此巴雷策法官表示最初的邀请被错误发送<ref name="nyt-specia-sept-16" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.computerweekly.com/news/252489051/MEPs-denied-access-as-observers-to-Julian-Assange-extradition-hearing|title=MEPs denied access as observers to Julian Assange extradition hearing|first=Sander|last=Priston|publisher=Computer Weekly|date=2020-09-15|access-date=2020-09-30|archive-date=2022-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220614132514/https://www.computerweekly.com/news/252489051/MEPs-denied-access-as-observers-to-Julian-Assange-extradition-hearing}}</ref>。最初被要求作为辩方证人作证的酷刑受害者{{tsl|en|Khaled el-Masri|哈立德·马斯里}}改以书面形式作证<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nuj.org.uk/news/assange-trial-hears-evidence-from-kahled-el-masri/|title=Assange trial hears evidence from Khaled el-Masri|first=Tim|last=Dawson|publisher=National Union of Journalists|date=2020-09-25|access-date=2020-09-29|archive-date=2021-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124061415/https://www.nuj.org.uk/news/assange-trial-hears-evidence-from-kahled-el-masri/}}</ref>。其他证人在证词中认为阿桑奇被引渡到美国后的监禁条件会更为恶劣，从而让阿桑奇[[亞斯伯格症候群|亞斯伯格症候群]]的抑郁和自杀倾向进一步加重<ref name="Asperger">{{cite web |url=https://www.computerweekly.com/news/252489508/Assange-has-Aspergers-syndrome-and-depression-court-hears |title=WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange has Asperger syndrome and depression, court hears |work=[[计算机周刊|Computer Weekly]] |date=2020-09-23 |access-date=2021-09-10 |author=Goodwin, Bill |archive-date=2022-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220604104735/https://www.computerweekly.com/news/252489508/Assange-has-Aspergers-syndrome-and-depression-court-hears }}</ref>。辩方在提上公开了一份监狱服务报告，显示狱警在搜查阿桑奇牢房时发现了一枚隐藏刀片<ref>{{cite web |title=Julian Assange faces 'torturous' months in parking space-sized cell if extradited to US, court hears |url=https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/julian-assange-faces-torturous-months-in-parking-space-sized-cell-if-extradited-to-us-court-hears/ |website=PressGazette |date=2020-09-28 |access-date=2021-09-05 |archive-date=2022-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519134545/https://pressgazette.co.uk/julian-assange-faces-torturous-months-in-parking-space-sized-cell-if-extradited-to-us-court-hears/ }}</ref>。法庭还透露阿桑奇曾多次联系[[撒瑪利亞會|撒瑪利亞會]]的防止自杀热线<ref>{{cite web |title=Julian Assange will not be extradited to US to face charges over WikiLeaks, judge rules |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/julian-assange-extradition-news-wikileaks-latest-us-b1781947.html |work=The Independent |date=2021-01-04 |access-date=2022-06-18 |archive-date=2022-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409070810/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/julian-assange-extradition-news-wikileaks-latest-us-b1781947.html }}</ref>。前[[美國陸軍刑事調查司令部|美國陸軍刑事調查司令部]]法医帕特里克·埃勒（Patrick Eller）表示阿桑奇没有美方所列的破解密码行为，因为切尔西故意只发送了密码哈希值的一部分。埃勒还表示密码破解是锤子前线作战基地（Forward Operating Base Hammer）驻扎士兵的共同话题，表明曼宁的信息与她已经拥有的机密文件无关<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/09/30/assange-extradition-cfaa-hacking/|title=Crumbling case against Assange shows weakness of 'hacking' charges related to whistleblowing|first=Micah|last=Lee|publisher=The Intercept|date=2020-09-30|access-date=2020-10-04|archive-date=2022-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220603023421/https://theintercept.com/2020/09/30/assange-extradition-cfaa-hacking/}}</ref>。9月30日的证词透露了UC环球监控厄瓜多尔大使馆的新指控。担心遭报复的前UC环球员工在庭上匿名作证，表示公司与特朗普政府代表[[謝爾登·阿德爾森|謝爾登·阿德爾森]]签订合同后，“行动越来越复杂”。该员工表示，情报部门特工曾计划闯入大使馆绑架或毒杀阿桑奇，打算获取阿桑奇孩子的DNA<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/sep/30/us-intelligence-sources-discussed-poisoning-julian-assange-court-told|title=US intelligence sources discussed poisoning Assange, court told|first=Ben|last=Quinn|work=The Guardian|date=2020-09-30|access-date=2020-10-04|archive-date=2021-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210929182527/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/sep/30/us-intelligence-sources-discussed-poisoning-julian-assange-court-told}}</ref>。听证会结束时，[[进步国际|进步国际]]仿照[[罗素法庭|罗素法庭]]举行贝尔马什法庭活动，深入审查“阿桑奇揭露的罪行，以及对他犯下的罪行”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.opendemocracy.net/en/oureconomy/belmarsh-tribunal/|title=The Belmarsh Tribunal|first=Srećko|last=Horvat|publisher=Open Democracy|date=2020-10-02|access-date=2020-10-07|archive-date=2022-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220622151306/https://www.opendemocracy.net/en/oureconomy/belmarsh-tribunal/}}</ref>。

听证会于2020年10月1日结束<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/world/wikileaks-assange-won-t-get-u-s-extradition-ruling-this-year-1.5128583|title=WikiLeaks' Assange won't get U.S. extradition ruling this year|first=Pan|last=Pylas|publisher=CTV News|date=2020-10-01|access-date=2020-10-04|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107022827/https://www.ctvnews.ca/world/wikileaks-assange-won-t-get-u-s-extradition-ruling-this-year-1.5128583}}</ref>。2021年1月4日，出于对阿桑奇心理健康的担忧，法官裁定不把阿桑奇引渡美国，避免他在美国监狱自杀<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-55528241|title=Julian Assange: Wikileaks founder refused extradition to US, judge rules|publisher=BBC|date=2021-01-04|access-date=2021-01-04|archive-date=2022-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220622205716/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-55528241}}</ref><ref name="NYT-ext-4jan">{{cite news |last1=Peltier |first1=Elian |last2=Specia |first2=Megan |title=U.K. Judge Blocks Assange's Extradition to U.S., Citing Mental Health Concerns |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/04/world/europe/assange-extradition-denied.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20211228/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/04/world/europe/assange-extradition-denied.html |archive-date=2021-12-28 |url-access=limited|access-date=2021-01-04 |work=The New York Times |date=2021-01-04}}{{cbignore}}</ref>。同时，法官其他所有问题上都支持美国一方，包括这些指控是否构成政治犯罪，以及他是否有权获得言论自由方面的保护<ref name="theduran.com">{{Cite web|date=2021-02-21|title=Assange defence mulls cross-appeal of January verdict, partner says|url=https://theduran.com/assange-defence-mulls-cross-appeal-of-january-verdict-partner-says/|access-date=2021-02-24|website=The Duran|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623003908/https://theduran.com/assange-defence-mulls-cross-appeal-of-january-verdict-partner-says/}}</ref>。

=== 上訴和其他發展 ===
其后，美國向英国高等法院上訴。10月27日，英国高等法院开庭审理美国的上诉。<ref>{{cite news |title=阿桑奇引渡案美国上诉 英国高院今天开审 |url=https://www.rfi.fr/cn/%E5%9B%BD%E9%99%85/20211027-%E9%98%BF%E6%A1%91%E5%A5%87%E5%BC%95%E6%B8%A1%E6%A1%88%E7%BE%8E%E5%9B%BD%E4%B8%8A%E8%AF%89-%E8%8B%B1%E5%9B%BD%E9%AB%98%E9%99%A2%E4%BB%8A%E5%A4%A9%E5%BC%80%E5%AE%A1 |accessdate=2021-10-28 |archive-date=2021-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127234944/https://www.rfi.fr/cn/%E5%9B%BD%E9%99%85/20211027-%E9%98%BF%E6%A1%91%E5%A5%87%E5%BC%95%E6%B8%A1%E6%A1%88%E7%BE%8E%E5%9B%BD%E4%B8%8A%E8%AF%89-%E8%8B%B1%E5%9B%BD%E9%AB%98%E9%99%A2%E4%BB%8A%E5%A4%A9%E5%BC%80%E5%AE%A1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>12月10日，英国高等法庭允许将阿桑奇引渡至美国受审<ref>{{cite news |title=英国法庭允许引渡“维基揭秘”创始人阿桑奇至美国受审 |url=http://shanghai.xinmin.cn/xmsq/2021/12/10/32078472.html |accessdate=2021-12-10 |archive-date=2021-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211210145827/http://shanghai.xinmin.cn/xmsq/2021/12/10/32078472.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2022年1月，英國[[英格蘭及威爾斯高等法院|高等法院]]批准[[維基解密|維基解密]]創辦人亞桑傑得以繼續就引渡美國案上訴至[[英国最高法院|最高法院]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=阿桑奇引渡案 英國高等法院批准上訴|url=https://www.hk01.com/即時國際/728122/阿桑奇引渡案-英國高等法院批准上訴|access-date=2022-01-25|date=2022-01-24|last=房伊媚|work=香港01|language=zh-HK|archive-date=2022-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125164436/https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B/728122/%E9%98%BF%E6%A1%91%E5%A5%87%E5%BC%95%E6%B8%A1%E6%A1%88-%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E9%AB%98%E7%AD%89%E6%B3%95%E9%99%A2%E6%89%B9%E5%87%86%E4%B8%8A%E8%A8%B4}}</ref>。

2022年3月，英国最高法院拒绝审理阿桑奇的引渡上诉案。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://apnews.com/article/technology-wikileaks-julian-assange-europe-becc5c90b75aaed730470b5741b50651 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2022-03-15 |archive-date=2022-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623003908/https://apnews.com/article/technology-wikileaks-julian-assange-europe-becc5c90b75aaed730470b5741b50651 }}</ref>

2022年4月20日，威斯敏斯特地方法院首席地方法官保罗·戈德斯普林正式批准将阿桑奇引渡到美国，并将决定提交给内政大臣[[普丽蒂·帕特尔|普丽蒂·帕特尔]](Priti Patel)<ref>{{Cite web|title=UK court approves extradition of Julian Assange to US|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2022/apr/20/uk-court-approves-extradition-of-julian-assange-to-us|access-date=2022-04-22|date=2022-04-20|work=the Guardian|language=en|archive-date=2022-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220622222419/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2022/apr/20/uk-court-approves-extradition-of-julian-assange-to-us}}</ref>。如果帕特尔批准法院的命令，阿桑奇可以通过司法审查对该决定提出上诉<ref>{{Cite news|title=UK judge sends extradition case of Wikileaks' Assange to interior minister Patel|url=https://www.reuters.com/world/uk/uk-judge-sends-extradition-case-wikileaks-assange-interior-minister-patel-2022-04-20/|newspaper=Reuters|date=2022-04-20|accessdate=2022-04-22|language=en|last=Reuters|archive-date=2022-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220626222339/https://www.reuters.com/world/uk/uk-judge-sends-extradition-case-wikileaks-assange-interior-minister-patel-2022-04-20/}}</ref>。

2022年6月17日，[[普丽蒂·帕特尔|帕特尔]]批准引渡<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2022/jun/17/julian-assange-extradition-to-us-approved-by-priti-patel|title=Julian Assange’s extradition from UK to US approved by home secretary|first1=Jamie|last1=Grierson|first2=Ben|last2=Quinn|publisher=The Guardian|date=17 June 2022|accessdate=2022-06-18|archive-date=2022-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220629065517/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2022/jun/17/julian-assange-extradition-to-us-approved-by-priti-patel}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=英国批准美国引渡维基解密创建人阿桑奇 {{!}} 早报 |url=https://www.zaobao.com.sg/realtime/world/story20220617-1284039 |website=www.zaobao.com.sg |language=zh-Hans |access-date=2022-06-17 |archive-date=2022-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623022829/https://www.zaobao.com.sg/realtime/world/story20220617-1284039 }}</ref>。 阿桑奇团队说他将要上诉<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/uk-govt-approves-extradition-of-assange-appeal-possible/2022/06/17/68f518c4-ee1f-11ec-9f90-79df1fb28296_story.html|title=UK govt orders Julian Assange's extradition; appeal planned|first=Jill|last=Lawless|publisher=The Washington Post|date=17 June 2022}}</ref>。

